Why we're testing this:
With your internal models (the 3 renamed ones), we want to see if THEY can do both steps reliably
If they can → LLM-driven tool calling is viable for your app
If they can't → procedural is the right choice (which we already proved)
The test captures EXACTLY what the LLM said, what it should have said, and what tool got called
Two distinct skills being tested:
Intent classification — Given "create a task for emp 3010", does the LLM correctly say "this is a CREATOR"?
Structured tool calling — Given it's a creator, does the LLM emit the correct JSON arguments for create_task(resource_id=3010, project_id=..., ...)?
These are independent failure modes. A model might classify correctly but fail at tool arguments, or vice versa.